yte wasn't an ordinary feline. After a particularly unfortunate encounter with a rogue delivery drone in 2042, a sympathetic underground ripperdoc had replaced her left eye with a high-definition optical sensor and her right front paw with a titanium-laced gripping claw. She was now 30% machine, 70% attitude, and 100% focused on finding the highest-grade synthetic tuna in the sector.\\\"]],[null,[null,0,\\\"The rain fell in shimmering digital streaks, reflecting off Byte’s optical sensor as she scanned the perimeter of a heavily guarded ramen stand. The proprietor, a grumpy cyborg with a neural interface plugged directly into his noodle-boiling vat, was known to throw scraps out the back door. But tonight, the back door was guarded by a pair of automated sentry turrets. Byte’s internal HUD flickered to life, overlaying the turrets' scanning cones in bright, wireframe red.\\\"]],[null,[null,0,\\\"She calculated the optimal trajectory. It required a triple-bounce off an adjacent neon sign, a mid-air twist to avoid the first sensor sweep, and a precision landing on a pile of discarded server racks. Byte initiated the sequence. Her cyber-paw hit the neon sign—CRACK—sending a shower of magenta sparks into the rain. She twisted, the titanium servos in her shoulder whining a quiet, high-pitched song of mechanical effort.\\\",[[265,270,[[null,null,null,null,1]]]]]],[null,[null,0,\\\"She landed silently on the server racks, just as a steaming chunk of synthetic tuna was tossed from the back door. Byte snatched it mid-air with her cybernetic claw, her optical sensor glowing a satisfied green. As she slinked back into the shadows to enjoy her prize, a nearby billboard flickered, displaying a vintage 2020 image of a man in a\\\"]]]]],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,false,[[[[1004,\\\"Länger\\\",5,null,[null,\\\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/i/short-term/release/googlesymbols/expand/default/24px.svg\\\",\\\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/